Who Pays for Australia’s EV Transition?

Surging Fuel Prices, Excise and Road‑User Charging (March 2026 update)

One‑line takeaway

Amid record pump‑price spikes and rapidly growing EV sales, a shrinking cohort of petrol drivers is still footing the bill for Australia’s roads; without an equitable distance‑based charge to replace fuel excise, the EV transition will transfer costs onto those least able to shoulder them.

